      "edited_at": "2025-09-17T09:29:14.268Z",
      "content": "<p>\u2026but a key resource tied to cgroups cannot actually participate in the delegation. Sniff! \ud83d\ude25</p><p>Well, no more! \ud83e\udd14</p><p>With v258 there are four new settings for unit files: BPFDelegateCommands=, BPFDelegateMaps=, BPFDelegatePrograms=, BPFDelegateAttachments=. These allow delegating certain BPF functionality to subcgroups, while prohibiting the rest. This hence allows fine grained delegation, breaking up the strict requirement to be privileged. \ud83e\udd13 \u2728</p>",
